            "text": "severe acute respiratory syndrome ( SARS )",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "due to coronavirus ( SARS - CoV ) and avian influenza A subtype H5N1 ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "is reviewed and compared based on the literature and the cases",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "examined by the authors . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Pneumocytes are the primary target of infection",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "resulting in diffuse alveolar damage . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Systemic cytokine activation results in hemophagocytic syndrome , lymphoid depletion , and skeletal muscle fiber necrosis . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "Severe acute respiratory syndrome induces a more fibrocellular intra - alveolar organization with a bbronchiolitis obliterans",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "organizing pneumoniaQ - like pattern and presence of multinucleated histiocytes and pneumocytes . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "H5N1 causes a more fulminant and necrotizing diffuse alveolar damage with patchy and interstitial paucicellular fibrosis . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Severe acute respiratory syndrome associated coronavirus persists in the lung up to the second month ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "whereas H5N1 persists in the lung up to the third week . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Severe acute respiratory syndrome associated coronavirus disseminates to blood , urine , feces , gastrointestinal tract , and liver . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "There is recent report of possible cerebral involvement by H5N1 and its isolation in the blood , gastrointestinal tract , and cerebrospinal fluid . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "More pathologic studies are urgently needed . <S> <P>",
